                                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                                      "width": "fill_container",
                                      "content": "Transformers and RNNs differ fundamentally in how they process sequences:\n\n1. Attention: Transformers use self-attention to relate all positions simultaneously (O(1) path length), while RNNs process sequentially (O(n) path length).\n\n2. Parallelization: Transformers process entire sequences in parallel during training; RNNs are inherently sequential, limiting GPU utilization.\n\n3. Long-range dependencies: Transformers handle these naturally; RNNs struggle with vanishing gradients over long sequences.",
                                      "lineHeight": 1.6,
                                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                                      "fontSize": 11,
                                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                                    }
